<taxonomicName authority="Zhao &amp; Zorn" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Zorn" authorityYear="2022" box="[1087,1381,1584,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Anomala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linwenhsini" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1087,1234,1584,1608]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">A. linwenhsini</emphasis>
Zhao &amp; Zorn
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="15" pageNumber="190" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype; D–G, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhao &amp; Zorn" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Zorn" authorityYear="2022" box="[406,689,1620,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Anomala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wutaiensis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[406,543,1620,1643]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">A. wutaiensis</emphasis>
Zhao &amp; Zorn
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[700,827,1619,1644]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[700,827,1619,1644]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype; H–J, N–O, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zorn &amp; Zhao" authorityName="Zorn &amp; Zhao" authorityYear="2022" box="[1061,1382,1620,1644]" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Anomala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kanshireiensis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[1061,1235,1620,1644]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">A. kanshireiensis</emphasis>
Zorn &amp; Zhao
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="15" pageNumber="190" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype; K–M, P–Q, 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhao &amp; Zorn" authorityName="Zhao &amp; Zorn" authorityYear="2022" box="[465,726,1656,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Anomala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inclinata" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[465,583,1656,1680]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">A. inclinata</emphasis>
Zhao &amp; Zorn
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[736,861,1655,1680]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[736,861,1655,1680]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype. A, D, H, K, dorsal view; B, F, I, L, N, P, right lateral view; E, O, Q, left lateral view; C, G, J, M, ventral view. Sc 1, scale bar for A–M = 2 mm; Sc 2, scale bar for N–Q = 5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1797,2040]" box="[199,1435,1797,1824]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,377,1797,1824]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
See 
<figureCitation box="[431,559,1798,1824]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1583,1607]" captionTargetBox="[163,1411,190,1552]" captionTargetId="figure-18@15.[151,1435,181,1560]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male genitalia (A–M) and everted endophallus (N–Q) of Anomala spp. A–C, A. linwenhsini Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype; D–G, A. wutaiensis Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype; H–J, N–O, A. kanshireiensis Zorn &amp; Zhao, new species, holotype; K–M, P–Q, A. inclinata Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype. A, D, H, K, dorsal view; B, F, I, L, N, P, right lateral view; E, O, Q, left lateral view; C, G, J, M, ventral view. Sc 1, scale bar for A–M = 2 mm; Sc 2, scale bar for N–Q = 5 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="190">Fig. 9K–M</figureCitation>
. Parameres asymmetric, right paramere longer. Ventral plate flat, apex arched.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1797,2040]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,408,1834,1860]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">
<typeStatus box="[199,310,1834,1860]" pageId="15" pageNumber="190">Paratype</typeStatus>
. Female
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[423,549,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[181,1411,404,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-106@13.[158,1430,381,1950]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Habitus of Anomala inclinata Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species. A–C, holotype; D–F, female paratype. A, D, dorsal view; B, E, lateral view; C, F, ventral view. Scale bar = 5 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="190">Figs. 7D–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[559,594,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,181,1857]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[151,1435,181,1857]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Head of Anomala spp. A, A. linwenhsini Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype; B, ditto, female paratype; C, A. wutaiensis Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype; D, ditto, female paratype; E, A. kanshireiensis Zorn &amp; Zhao, new species, holotype; F, ditto, female paratype; G, A. inclinata Zhao &amp; Zorn, new species, holotype; H, ditto, female paratype. Scale bar = 5 mm." pageId="15" pageNumber="190">8H</figureCitation>
). Body length: 
<quantity box="[767,868,1834,1861]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="15" pageNumber="190" unit="mm" value="13.5">13.5 mm</quantity>
, greatest width: 
<quantity box="[1049,1137,1834,1860]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.9" pageId="15" pageNumber="190" unit="mm" value="6.9">6.9 mm</quantity>
. Generally similar to male. Antennal club almost equally as long as antennomeres 2–6 combined. Pygidium more bulging, shorter than in male. Protibia and protarsomeres thinner than in male; apical protibial tooth tongue-shaped, almost extends to level of apex of protarsomere 2; other two teeth blunt at apex, the third one indistinct; inner spur situated at the level of the third tooth; internomedial protuberance of protarsomere 5 small; upper and lower branches of inner protarsal claw and outer mesotarsal claw almost equal in length. Ventral metathoracic surface less setose than in male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1371,150,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="191" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,150,285]" box="[199,1371,150,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,462,150,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="191">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
See differential diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zorn &amp; Zhao" authorityName="Zorn &amp; Zhao" authorityYear="2022" box="[790,1214,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Rutelidae" genus="Anomala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kanshireiensis" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[790,1057,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="191">Anomala kanshireiensis</emphasis>
Zorn &amp; Zhao
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1226,1363,150,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="191">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1226,1363,150,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="191" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="191" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,150,285]" pageId="16" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,187,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="191">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet derives from the Latin adjective “ 
<emphasis box="[945,1150,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="191">inclinatus, -a, -um</emphasis>
”, alluding to the inclined parameres of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
